Where Intelligence Sits
The risk across three execution substrates (Fusion / Copilot Studio / MCP) is duplicated intelligence. Resolved by assigning each job exactly one home.
Job	Home	Rule
Compute (gap rules, pattern benchmarks, risk scoring)	NBA engine	One brain. The only place intelligence is calculated.
Define (TD fields, touchpoint types, stage-gates)	Canonical knowledge base	Authored once; referenced by NBA rules, agents, and MCP — never re-authored per surface.
Reason / converse (NLU, answer composition)	Copilot agents	Reason about language, not priorities. Read NBA output; never rank.
Access / transport	MCP server	The doorway, not the brain. Exposes NBA outputs and the knowledge base.
The principle: compute once (NBA), define once (knowledge base), expose everywhere (MCP), deliver conversationally (agents) — never recompute downstream.
If you changed a stage-gate tomorrow, you should edit exactly two things — NBA logic and the one definition. If it is four, intelligence has leaked.
